What is the value of y in the output of this code?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
void main () {
    int x = 3, y = 2;
    switch(x + 4){
    case 6: y = 0;
    case 7: y = 1;
    default : y += 2;
    }
    cout << y << endl;
}
```

What is the output of the following arithmetic operation?

Assume the input is **4**

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
void main () {
    int x; cin >> x;
    double result = x + 2 * 3.25 - 6 % 4;
    cout << result << endl;
}
```

What is the output of the following code?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
void main () {
    int found = 0, count = 5;
    if(found == 0 && count-- == 0)
        cout << "danger" << endl;
    cout << "count = " << count << endl;
}
```

What is the output of the following code?

Assume the input is: **4 11**

```cpp
